headline: Carvana earnings, Fed minutes, housing data: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Alexandra Canal outline key events investors should monitor for Wednesday, February 19. On the earnings calendar, Wingstop (WING), Etsy (ETSY), and Conagra Brands (CAG) will report quarterly results before the market opens, while Carvana (CVNA) and Toast (TOST) will release their earnings reports later in the afternoon. Investors will closely analyze the minutes from the Federal Reserve's January FOMC meeting. These minutes, along with scheduled remarks from Fed Vice Chair Philip Jefferson, should provide deeper insight into the central bank's monetary policy outlook. Additionally, new US housing starts and building permits data will be released. Economists anticipate January housing starts to reach 1.39 million and permits to hit 1.46 million, both figures showing declines from December levels. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Angel Smith

headline: Why Conagra Stock Tumbled by Nearly 6% on Tuesday
summary: The market didn't find the stock of Conagra Brands (NYSE: CAG) very tasty on the first trading day of the week after the holiday weekend.  Conagra revealed the new outlook for its fiscal 2025, and it's no wonder investors found it wanting.  It also shaved its forecast for non-GAAP (generally accepted accounting principles) adjusted earnings per share.

headline: Why Conagra (CAG) Stock Is Down Today
summary: Shares of packaged foods company Conagra Brands (NYSE:CAG) fell 7.7% in the morning session after the company reported underwhelming preliminary full-year 2025 guidance and expects sales and profits to be below its previous forecast. Precisely, the company expects full-year earnings of about $2.35 (vs. previous guidance of $2.45 to $2.50 per share). Organic sales are also expected to decline by 2% year on year (vs previous guidance of a decline between 1.5% and flat growth).

headline: Conagra, Robinhood, Meta all slip: Market Minute
summary: Afternoon trading was muted as investors await earnings and the latest moves from the Trump administration. Conagra Brands (CAG) was one of the stocks moving to the downside after lowering its fiscal 2025 outlook. Robinhood's (HOOD) stock was also under pressure after being downgraded to Perform from Outperform at Wolfe Research. Meta shares are trading slightly lower, with the stock on the verge of snapping its streak of 20-sessions of gains. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
